    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Historical term for tribunals in the Netherlands that were in use from the Middle Ages until the Ancien Régime, and that administered grievances before lawmaking and a judiciary were formalized into separate entities.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
